name: PerformanceTiming.domainLookupStart
description: The legacy PerformanceTiming.domainLookupStart read-only property returns an unsigned long long representing the moment, in miliseconds since the UNIX epoch, where the domain lookup starts. If a persistent connection is used, or the information is stored in a cache or a local resource, the value will be the same as PerformanceTiming.fetchStart.
